# Slidev Export Skill

Use the Slidev CLI to export your deck to PDF (or other formats) for sharing and delivery.

## Primary command (repo default)

From the `slidev/` folder:

```
npm run export -- --format pdf
```

This uses the local `@slidev/cli` and exports the deck defined by `slides.md`.

## Export options (detailed)

`slidev export [entry]`

- `[entry]` (default: `slides.md`): Path to the markdown file containing slides.
- `--output`: Output path. Defaults to `exportFilename` (frontmatter) or `[entry]-export`.
- `--format`: Output format. Supported values: `pdf`, `png`, `pptx`, `md`. Default: `pdf`.
- `--timeout`: Print-page render timeout in ms. Default: `30000`.
- `--range`: Page ranges to export, e.g. `1,4-5,6`.
- `--dark`: Export in dark theme mode.
- `--with-clicks` / `-c`: Export pages for every click animation.
- `--theme` / `-t`: Override theme.
- `--omit-background`: Remove default browser background.

## Examples

Export to PDF with a custom output name:

```
npm run export -- --format pdf --output rules-commands-skills.pdf
```

Export only selected slides:

```
npm run export -- --range "1,4-5,6"
```

Export with click animations:

```
npm run export -- --with-clicks
```

